1
00:00:00,042 --> 00:00:01,627
A lot of people are watching this case.

2
00:00:01,711 --> 00:00:03,921
But not all of them
are interested in the truth.

3
00:00:10,094 --> 00:00:11,721
A lot of people noticed

4
00:00:11,804 --> 00:00:14,432
that the detective talked
to you here yesterday.

5
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:16,475
Some are even saying
Anton might be involved.

6
00:00:16,559 --> 00:00:19,770
How long were you planning
to hide that you met with Sam?

7
00:00:19,854 --> 00:00:22,523
Don't tell me you believe
what that detective said.

8
00:00:22,606 --> 00:00:25,401
I just don't understand
why you're still avoiding me.

9
00:00:25,484 --> 00:00:27,194
Teacher Sam is gone now. No one--

10
00:00:28,279 --> 00:00:30,197
Don't ever mention that name again, okay?

11
00:00:30,281 --> 00:00:31,365
Jackie.

12
00:00:31,449 --> 00:00:33,033
Sam is here.

13
00:00:44,003 --> 00:00:45,796
Good luck!

14
00:00:56,265 --> 00:00:59,143
If you're happy, show it and laugh

15
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:03,481
If you're happy, show it and laugh

16
00:01:04,482 --> 00:01:08,402
If you're happy, life will be more fun

17
00:01:08,486 --> 00:01:11,864
If you're happy, show it and laugh

18
00:01:12,865 --> 00:01:16,035
If you're happy, clap your hands

19
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:20,164
If you're happy, clap your hands

20
00:01:20,915 --> 00:01:25,544
If you're happy, life will be more fun

21
00:01:25,628 --> 00:01:28,255
If you're happy, clap your hands

22
00:01:32,051 --> 00:01:34,345
Good job, son!

23
00:02:05,543 --> 00:02:10,464
Thank you so much
for supporting our program.

24
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:14,844
Let's give our first batch
a round of applause.

25
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:23,811
As a daughter of deaf parents,

26
00:02:24,854 --> 00:02:29,525
it has always been my dream
to have a special education program

27
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:31,068
here in Escondido.

28
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:36,156
So, thank you so much,
Mayor Serge Dominguez…

29
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:41,579
for helping us get the funds

30
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:46,417
and sponsors to continue
our little program.

31
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:54,091
I believe in the voice of the youth,
and it comes in all forms.

32
00:02:55,134 --> 00:02:57,845
I know that their voices

33
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:01,473
have a place in our country's future.

34
00:03:06,604 --> 00:03:07,980
Thank you.

35
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,353
Anton?

36
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:15,315
Anton, is that you?

37
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:17,860
Anton?

38
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:20,279
Anton.

39
00:05:26,201 --> 00:05:27,411
Anton, is that you?

40
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,004
Anton.

41
00:05:48,265 --> 00:05:49,558
Anton.

42
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:56,315
What happened to you?

43
00:05:57,983 --> 00:05:59,026
Are you okay?

44
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,479
Hey, why are you standing up?

45
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:39,358
The doctor said you need to rest.
You're still under observation.

46
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:41,985
I'm fine. I'm not badly hur--

47
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:55,082
-Where is…
-Are you looking for this?

48
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:09,555
"Theodore P. Ignacio."

49
00:07:10,806 --> 00:07:16,228
He's Sam's brother who would show up
here in Escondido and then leave.

50
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,564
That explains why
he has access to the house.

51
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:21,733
It seemed he was running away
or hiding something.

52
00:07:22,985 --> 00:07:27,739
Did you find the bag with initials?

53
00:07:27,823 --> 00:07:30,909
-The one with the money?
-Negative.

54
00:07:30,993 --> 00:07:32,953
We didn't find anything
besides that wallet.

55
00:07:33,537 --> 00:07:34,705
It's gone, then.

56
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:37,624
He already got away and he's hiding now.

57
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:40,335
That is, if he gets past
the checkpoint areas.

58
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:45,257
An order has been issued to find him
and arrest him for questioning.

59
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:46,884
Well?

60
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:51,096
Are you now convinced
that Sam Ignacio didn't commit suicide?

61
00:07:53,557 --> 00:07:56,393
That there's a deeper truth to this case?

62
00:08:01,148 --> 00:08:05,360
If the kids see this,
they'll ask what happened to you.

63
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:07,738
What were you thinking?

64
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,824
I was only letting out my frustrations.

65
00:08:12,034 --> 00:08:14,661
I don't understand
why I got involved in this issue.

66
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:17,080
People are now thinking that I'm…

67
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:21,460
That I'm a criminal.

68
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:25,088
Sam was also my friend.

69
00:08:25,172 --> 00:08:26,548
She was our friend, right?

70
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:29,426
Why would people think
I had a hand in her death?

71
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:32,429
Anton.

72
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:36,433
We can't control
what people want to believe.

73
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:39,770
What if…

74
00:08:40,646 --> 00:08:43,023
What if they find out about my past?

75
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:47,527
What, do they think
Sam and I had an affair?

76
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:50,447
Well, did you?

77
00:08:56,495 --> 00:08:57,579
No, Jackie.

78
00:08:59,331 --> 00:09:01,041
We never had an affair.

79
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,794
I made a promise to you, remember?

80
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:06,588
And I haven't broken that promise.

81
00:09:10,801 --> 00:09:14,429
I'm just scared
that our children will find out

82
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:20,644
about my past and what I did wrong
because I'm being linked to Sam's death.

83
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:24,231
If they ask questions,
we won't hide anything.

84
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:27,317
We'll tell them the truth.

85
00:09:31,947 --> 00:09:34,074
Come on. Let's go back there.

86
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,727
Keep your mouth shut if you don't want
to end up like your sister.

87
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,074
He's headed there.

88
00:11:03,914 --> 00:11:05,332
Stop! Hands up!

89
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:12,798
Go. Cuff him.

90
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:43,763
What's wrong?

91
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:46,391
Are you okay?

92
00:12:48,894 --> 00:12:52,147
Yes, don't worry. I'm just a little tired.

93
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,648
But I'm beside you now.

94
00:12:53,732 --> 00:12:57,277
My energy-booster!

95
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:12,417
You seem lost in thought.

96
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,252
Are you okay?

97
00:13:16,046 --> 00:13:17,130
It's nothing, Ma.

98
00:13:17,214 --> 00:13:19,591
I just saw Matteo leave.

99
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:21,676
I guess he only came here for the food.

100
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:25,847
Well, you know how your brother is.

101
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:29,643
You should get some food too.
Take Eli with you.

102
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:32,687
Go get some food over there.

103
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:33,688
Yes?

104
00:13:33,772 --> 00:13:34,981
This is she.

105
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,109
-Ted?
-What about Ted?

106
00:13:38,193 --> 00:13:39,861
He was shot?

107
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:43,532
-He got in trouble again.
-Which hospital?

108
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:44,616
What was Ted thinking?

109
00:13:44,699 --> 00:13:46,076
I'm going there.

110
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:47,869
Yes, I'm going there.

111
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:51,706
My goodness! Come on.

112
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,333
Let's go.

113
00:13:55,627 --> 00:13:57,963
What happened?

114
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:07,264
Okay, ma'am.

115
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:10,559
-Ma'am, I need assistance.
-Sam…

116
00:14:10,642 --> 00:14:12,394
-Sam's the reason…
-I need assistance.

117
00:14:12,477 --> 00:14:13,603
-Hurry.
-Ted.

118
00:14:14,437 --> 00:14:15,730
What do you mean?

119
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:18,024
Do you and your sister have a problem?

120
00:14:18,108 --> 00:14:19,359
-Assistance, please.
-With who?

121
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:20,402
That's enough, sir.

122
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:21,486
-We're taking the patient in.
-Ted.

123
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,780
-We're taking the patient inside.
-Excuse me, sir.

124
00:14:26,449 --> 00:14:29,452
Ted! Where is Ted?

125
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:31,246
Nurse, I'm here for Ted Ignacio.

126
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:32,831
Oh, my god…

127
00:14:33,832 --> 00:14:35,208
Ted!

128
00:14:44,676 --> 00:14:45,760
Thank you.

129
00:14:56,479 --> 00:14:58,148
Ted is a complicated person.

130
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:01,860
Trouble just won't leave him alone.

131
00:15:03,278 --> 00:15:06,448
And now, he's caught up
in his sister's issue.

132
00:15:06,990 --> 00:15:09,534
Does Ted get into trouble a lot?

133
00:15:09,618 --> 00:15:11,578
Just something we cousins joke about.

134
00:15:11,661 --> 00:15:14,122
Ted's really a valedictorian.

135
00:15:14,205 --> 00:15:16,583
Valedictorian of mischief.

136
00:15:20,503 --> 00:15:22,672
He's always given Sam a hard time.

137
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:26,301
Didn't Sam ever try to fix her brother?

138
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:31,514
She did. But it always ended in a fight.

139
00:15:31,598 --> 00:15:35,894
In one of their worst fights,
Sam was furious.

140
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:41,650
She threatened to expose Ted
to the press about what she knew.

141
00:15:44,611 --> 00:15:47,822
It would be a huge scandal
if the media got interested.

142
00:15:51,493 --> 00:15:52,994
What was that?

143
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:02,337
Chief, can you give us
even a small lead regarding the Ignacios?

144
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:05,507
I can't say anything
until an official report is released.

145
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:07,384
We just want some clarity.
Even just a little bit of info.

146
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:10,929
It's better to wait
than to get the data wrong.

147
00:16:11,012 --> 00:16:12,847
-It's the mayor!
-Mayor!

148
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:14,224
-Mayor!
-Mayor.

149
00:16:19,062 --> 00:16:21,981
Sam is going to scold us for this.

150
00:16:22,065 --> 00:16:24,818
She's allergic to sad vibes.

151
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,824
At least you're okay.

152
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:34,327
I know you need something.

153
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:37,205
What is it?

154
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:39,290
Did they tell you?

155
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:41,918
You'll be one of those giving a eulogy.

156
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:44,212
If that's okay.

157
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,344
What's going on?

158
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:56,683
Mayor! Do you have a suspect
in the shooting of Ted Ignacio?

159
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:58,643
He's the brother of the teacher
who just passed away.

160
00:16:58,727 --> 00:17:01,938
Is Sam Ignacio's case
connected to the shooting of her brother?

161
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:05,400
Is suicide still the angle
in Sam Ignacio's death?

162
00:17:08,862 --> 00:17:10,280
The detective is here.

163
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:12,323
Detective Cortez!

164
00:17:12,407 --> 00:17:14,951
Any information
about the shooting of Ted Ignacio?

165
00:17:23,585 --> 00:17:27,756
It was confirmed this morning
that Theodore "Ted" Ignacio was shot.

166
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:30,842
He is the brother of the late Sam Ignacio.

167
00:17:30,925 --> 00:17:34,512
He is currently in the hospital
and in stable condition.

168
00:17:34,596 --> 00:17:37,098
We are still investigating this incident.

169
00:17:37,182 --> 00:17:39,559
Is this incident connected
to Sam Ignacio's death?

170
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:42,896
Does this mean you are investigating
the Ignacio family again?

171
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:45,648
Is there a person of interest
in the shooting?

172
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:49,652
We are looking into all possible angles.

173
00:17:50,153 --> 00:17:55,116
But, sir, is the ruling on Sam's death
clearly still suicide?

174
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,286
For now, we are not changing
the official findings.

175
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:01,873
So, you aren't dismissing
the possibility of foul play?

176
00:18:07,045 --> 00:18:09,964
We aren't dismissing any possibilities.

177
00:18:10,465 --> 00:18:13,384
My god, it looks like Sam's death
wasn't a suicide after all.

178
00:18:13,468 --> 00:18:15,553
Does that mean she was killed?

179
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:31,945
Just go home for now.
I'll update you about the eulogy, okay?

180
00:18:36,241 --> 00:18:37,492
We should go home for now.

181
00:18:38,785 --> 00:18:39,911
Come on.

182
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:48,920
Listen up.

183
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:53,758
We assure the public that there will be
a fair investigation into this case.

184
00:18:53,842 --> 00:18:55,718
But for now,

185
00:18:55,802 --> 00:18:58,429
our primary goal is to ensure the safety

186
00:18:58,513 --> 00:19:01,182
of all citizens of the town of Escondido.

187
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:02,976
Thank you so much.

188
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:04,894
-Thank you, Mayor.
-Thank you, Mayor.

189
00:19:19,576 --> 00:19:21,411
Oh, Ma'am Sam.

190
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:25,123
Yes. Was she here often?

191
00:19:25,206 --> 00:19:29,002
They said you know.
You're usually the last janitor to leave.

192
00:19:29,836 --> 00:19:33,715
The mayor doesn't want the office messy
when he arrives in the morning.

193
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:36,926
It has to be neat and clean
before I head out.

194
00:19:37,468 --> 00:19:40,722
Except for when Ma'am Sam visited.

195
00:19:43,016 --> 00:19:43,933
Why is that?

196
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:47,770
I'm not allowed to go in there,
especially when Ma'am Sam is inside.

197
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:52,734
Anyway, sir, I have to go.

198
00:19:52,817 --> 00:19:54,819
I still need to clean the bathrooms.

199
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:19,177
Is this the one, sir?

200
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,012
Yes. Go ahead and zoom in.

201
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:56,422
Sorry, I didn't see you either.

202
00:20:56,506 --> 00:20:58,341
It's my fault. I wasn't looking.

203
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:00,134
-I'm sorry.
-My apologies too.

204
00:21:02,011 --> 00:21:02,845
Alright.

205
00:21:06,808 --> 00:21:09,143
I was also going to ask…

206
00:21:09,894 --> 00:21:12,063
is suicide still not ruled out?

207
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:15,692
I heard you already have
a new lead in the case.

208
00:21:19,404 --> 00:21:20,363
Ma'am…

209
00:21:21,239 --> 00:21:24,075
You're one of the victim's
closest friends.

210
00:21:24,158 --> 00:21:27,954
Did you notice anything strange?

211
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,874
Did she seem tired or stressed?
Or pressured at work?

212
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,626
Any sign she was harassed?

213
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:38,339
Was Ms. Ignacio paid to do
something she didn't want to?

214
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:40,967
Paid to do something?

215
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:45,471
What are you saying, sir?
That Sam was accepting bribes?

216
00:21:47,265 --> 00:21:49,892
Sir, Sam wasn't that kind of person.

217
00:21:49,976 --> 00:21:52,854
Do you really have to tarnish
my friend's memory?

218
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:55,815
What exactly are you looking for?

219
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:59,444
Anything, as long as it's the truth.

220
00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:03,406
Even if something gets destroyed.
Even if someone gets hurt.

221
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:06,451
And you, Mrs. Carpio…

222
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,662
How well did you know your friend?

223
00:22:39,776 --> 00:22:40,818
Let's eat.

224
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:44,655
I'm still finishing something.

225
00:22:44,739 --> 00:22:46,991
I'll wait for you so we can eat together.

226
00:22:50,745 --> 00:22:54,373
It's okay, I'll just finish it later.

227
00:22:56,793 --> 00:22:57,919
Let's go.

228
00:23:40,586 --> 00:23:43,589
You've been there for a while.
Aren't you going to rest?

229
00:23:44,715 --> 00:23:46,050
I'm almost done.

230
00:23:46,134 --> 00:23:49,178
-Can I read it?
-No.

231
00:23:53,516 --> 00:23:55,434
You'll hear it, anyway.

232
00:23:56,227 --> 00:23:59,188
I'm sure you have beautiful things
to say about Sam.

233
00:24:05,027 --> 00:24:07,113
Finish it so you can get some sleep.

234
00:24:29,677 --> 00:24:30,845
And you, Mrs. Carpio…

235
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:34,265
How well did you know your friend?

236
00:24:59,749 --> 00:25:04,170
So, to all her students and co-teachers,

237
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:07,465
please treasure her memories.

238
00:25:09,008 --> 00:25:10,635
We love you, Sam.

239
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:14,430
Thank you.

240
00:25:48,506 --> 00:25:51,842
I can't describe Sam as…

241
00:25:53,261 --> 00:25:55,096
as a perfect person.

242
00:25:58,140 --> 00:26:00,142
Maybe it's easier if…

243
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:06,565
if I describe her as someone
who's hard to love.

244
00:26:13,281 --> 00:26:14,824
Like?

245
00:26:14,907 --> 00:26:18,244
First, Sam was stubborn.

246
00:26:23,416 --> 00:26:25,543
When she sees something wrong,

247
00:26:26,627 --> 00:26:28,087
she doesn't know how to stay silent.

248
00:26:28,170 --> 00:26:29,588
Miss Jackie, just a moment, okay?

249
00:26:34,051 --> 00:26:35,344
He just isn't the right fit.

250
00:26:36,012 --> 00:26:38,806
Not a good fit
or are you just uncomfortable?

251
00:26:38,889 --> 00:26:42,226
Teacher Sam, we need a school guard.

252
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:45,438
There are protocols and safety concerns.

253
00:26:45,521 --> 00:26:47,106
Because he's hard of hearing?

254
00:26:48,190 --> 00:26:49,525
Ma'am, take a look.

255
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:54,905
He has training, experience,
and recommendations.

256
00:26:54,989 --> 00:26:56,907
What do you think is missing?

257
00:26:56,991 --> 00:27:00,494
We have a SPED program
at this school, right?

258
00:27:00,578 --> 00:27:02,705
Every day, we teach our students

259
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:04,957
that they're capable
and that they have a place in this world.

260
00:27:05,041 --> 00:27:07,668
But when it comes
to our own school, we say…

261
00:27:07,752 --> 00:27:10,296
"Sorry, your place ends in the classroom."

262
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:14,425
If we can't give opportunities
to people with disabilities,

263
00:27:14,508 --> 00:27:18,804
then we have no right
to call ourselves inclusive.

264
00:27:18,888 --> 00:27:20,056
Look!

265
00:27:21,599 --> 00:27:26,020
So, please review it again, okay?

266
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:33,611
Do this because we have a responsibility
to the students we teach here.

267
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:48,959
Second, a lot of people
were won over by Sam.

268
00:27:50,461 --> 00:27:52,129
I was one of them.

269
00:27:52,213 --> 00:27:54,465
It always felt like
she brought sunlight with her.

270
00:28:02,431 --> 00:28:05,601
For Sam, the world was normal.

271
00:28:06,727 --> 00:28:07,770
Safe.

272
00:28:09,355 --> 00:28:11,899
-You felt like you mattered.
-Where's Eli?

273
00:28:11,982 --> 00:28:13,692
Oh, no!

274
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:15,361
-For her...
-Where are you, Eli?

275
00:28:15,444 --> 00:28:17,196
Eli didn't have to be different.

276
00:28:17,279 --> 00:28:20,199
I think he went home. Did he go home?

277
00:28:20,908 --> 00:28:22,618
Oh, no!

278
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:26,997
He wasn't lacking anything.

279
00:28:28,249 --> 00:28:29,208
He was just happy.

280
00:28:30,793 --> 00:28:32,253
-Free.
-Got you!

281
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:35,214
I saw you!

282
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:38,592
Like a…

283
00:28:40,428 --> 00:28:41,679
butterfly?

284
00:28:47,143 --> 00:28:48,936
But what I've learned is that…

285
00:28:50,855 --> 00:28:53,482
bringing light into others' lives…

286
00:28:55,443 --> 00:28:57,736
doesn't make you immune to being blinded.

287
00:29:01,907 --> 00:29:04,577
Jackie knows already. Did you tell her?

288
00:29:05,286 --> 00:29:07,746
You should've thought it through
before starting this mess.

289
00:29:10,499 --> 00:29:11,959
You think I started this mess?

290
00:29:12,710 --> 00:29:14,044
Me?

291
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:17,673
Anton, I didn't tell Jackie anything.

292
00:29:24,263 --> 00:29:26,056
Sam, I'm begging you.

293
00:29:26,557 --> 00:29:29,768
Jackie will leave me.
She'll take our children away from me.

294
00:29:31,353 --> 00:29:32,438
Sam…

295
00:29:55,336 --> 00:29:57,755
Sometimes, she cared too much.

296
00:29:58,881 --> 00:30:00,341
To…

297
00:30:01,425 --> 00:30:04,261
To the point of being meddlesome.

298
00:30:05,137 --> 00:30:06,430
I know, ma'am.

299
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:10,267
I'll tell Mama.

300
00:30:10,351 --> 00:30:12,645
It's just that we can't find
the right timing.

301
00:30:12,728 --> 00:30:16,482
We're also scared
of telling his father first.

302
00:30:17,608 --> 00:30:19,276
It's true, isn't it?

303
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,655
-You're scared of him.
-That's not the point!

304
00:30:23,197 --> 00:30:24,865
Matteo?

305
00:30:24,949 --> 00:30:25,991
Matteo.

306
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:29,537
Matteo, this isn't for me.

307
00:30:30,204 --> 00:30:31,580
This is for you two.

308
00:30:32,206 --> 00:30:34,375
I know you're confused right now.

309
00:30:35,167 --> 00:30:36,877
You're both scared, especially you.

310
00:30:36,961 --> 00:30:39,964
Having a child is a heavy responsibility,

311
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:42,424
especially at your age.

312
00:30:42,925 --> 00:30:44,301
So…

313
00:30:45,219 --> 00:30:48,305
it's important that you get
guidance and support

314
00:30:48,389 --> 00:30:50,099
from your parents now more than ever.

315
00:30:51,016 --> 00:30:55,521
The sooner you tell them,
the sooner things will get easier.

316
00:31:03,654 --> 00:31:05,823
And what seems to be a mystery to many…

317
00:31:12,997 --> 00:31:15,374
is where Sam got her courage.

318
00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:20,546
She wasn't afraid to take risks.

319
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:27,344
Okay. I'll get going now, okay?

320
00:31:27,428 --> 00:31:28,512
Bye, Sam.

321
00:31:28,596 --> 00:31:30,139
-Bye. Take care.
-You too.

322
00:31:30,222 --> 00:31:32,558
Even if she knew it was dangerous…

323
00:31:33,392 --> 00:31:36,312
Please, Sam. Just let this one go.

324
00:31:36,395 --> 00:31:39,315
I already accepted it.
It won't happen again.

325
00:31:42,109 --> 00:31:43,902
Look, I don't want to get
in trouble with the mayor.

326
00:31:50,159 --> 00:31:53,537
No. That's not part of the agreement, Ted.

327
00:31:53,621 --> 00:31:55,414
Just think of it
as a token of gratitude from him.

328
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:57,082
I said, return it!

329
00:31:57,166 --> 00:31:59,460
Think of how it can help
the children's foundation.

330
00:31:59,543 --> 00:32:01,211
Leave the kids out of this, Ted.

331
00:32:02,171 --> 00:32:04,673
I know what that money is really for.

332
00:32:04,757 --> 00:32:08,260
My conscience can't bear it.
So you'd better return it.

333
00:32:08,344 --> 00:32:11,930
If you don't, I'll return it myself.

334
00:32:25,194 --> 00:32:26,695
Yes, Sam.

335
00:32:27,738 --> 00:32:30,366
I agreed to talk in front of everyone

336
00:32:32,076 --> 00:32:34,328
just to berate you.

337
00:32:41,627 --> 00:32:44,838
To tell you how angry I am with you.

338
00:33:09,530 --> 00:33:12,491
Because you were so stubborn.

339
00:33:14,535 --> 00:33:18,455
You keep trying to fix
other people's problems.

340
00:33:39,810 --> 00:33:41,687
And because Sam was like that…

341
00:33:43,439 --> 00:33:46,442
she never turned her back on anyone.

342
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:51,739
Even when she knew
there were consequences.

343
00:33:53,574 --> 00:33:57,286
Even when she knew
that in the end, she'd pay for it.

344
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:04,543
That's why I refuse to believe
that Sam gave up on life.

345
00:34:08,505 --> 00:34:11,717
If you're one of the people
she once helped,

346
00:34:14,136 --> 00:34:15,971
at least once…

347
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:23,103
If you are one of the people
whose lives she touched…

348
00:34:30,444 --> 00:34:32,696
please don't accept the assumption

349
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:36,784
that she chose to end her story
by giving up.

350
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:57,739
I know this couldn't
have been Sam's choice.

351
00:35:59,032 --> 00:36:01,243
And if something else
did happen that night,

352
00:36:02,536 --> 00:36:04,288
I'll find out what it was.

353
00:36:24,766 --> 00:36:28,103
Meet me at the corner of Rodriguez
and Quejano Street at 10.

354
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:32,441
There's something you need to know
about Samantha Ignacio's case.

355
00:36:57,507 --> 00:36:59,593
Matteo, where are you?

356
00:36:59,676 --> 00:37:02,763
I won't cover for you
if they ask where you are.

357
00:37:05,432 --> 00:37:06,600
Ma.

358
00:37:21,531 --> 00:37:23,742
I'll just head back to school.

359
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:25,410
To help out.

360
00:37:28,038 --> 00:37:29,206
Ma.

361
00:37:30,332 --> 00:37:32,876
Isn't the wake over?

362
00:37:34,836 --> 00:37:38,048
There are still some things
we have to take care of.

363
00:37:38,799 --> 00:37:42,386
We also have to meet in preparation
for the students' grief counseling.

364
00:37:43,011 --> 00:37:44,513
I won't take long.

365
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:54,940
-I'll leave Eli to you.
-Yes, Ma.

366
00:37:55,023 --> 00:37:57,693
Sleep early. Don't wait up for me.

367
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:22,968
Mr. Carpio!

368
00:38:29,391 --> 00:38:30,517
Anton!

369
00:38:32,019 --> 00:38:33,145
Mayor.

370
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:34,855
You're working out this late?

371
00:38:38,942 --> 00:38:40,777
You know my father?

372
00:38:40,861 --> 00:38:42,571
Yeah, I've known him for a while.

373
00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:44,239
He's part of Dad's legal team.

374
00:38:45,115 --> 00:38:47,117
Sharp, quiet…

375
00:38:47,701 --> 00:38:49,327
Loyal to the end.

376
00:38:53,582 --> 00:38:55,751
I'm just looking for someone
to fill a vacant position

377
00:38:55,834 --> 00:38:57,961
at the Able Hearts Foundation.

378
00:38:59,004 --> 00:39:00,839
Able Hearts?

379
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:02,382
You're the one I thought of.

380
00:39:08,096 --> 00:39:10,432
But I have to think about it

381
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:12,809
and check with the uni and my wife.

382
00:39:13,769 --> 00:39:14,811
No problem.

383
00:39:15,437 --> 00:39:17,230
You don't rush the right person.

384
00:39:19,066 --> 00:39:20,233
Let's talk again later?

385
00:39:20,942 --> 00:39:22,402
-Sure, Mayor. Thank you.
-Thank you.

386
00:39:23,445 --> 00:39:24,780
Thank you.

387
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:25,822
Take care, Mayor.

388
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:13,203
You?

389
00:40:32,180 --> 00:40:34,975
You said your goal is to find the truth.

390
00:40:38,311 --> 00:40:39,896
That's my job, ma'am.

391
00:40:41,982 --> 00:40:44,985
And you? Why are you doing this?

392
00:40:45,068 --> 00:40:47,112
Sam was a good friend.

393
00:40:48,697 --> 00:40:50,532
She was like a mother to my kids.

394
00:40:52,075 --> 00:40:53,285
Especially to Eli.

395
00:40:54,327 --> 00:40:55,787
Like I've told you before,

396
00:40:56,955 --> 00:41:00,333
seeking the truth can be complicated.

397
00:41:01,710 --> 00:41:04,462
It gets messy and painful.

398
00:41:06,006 --> 00:41:07,549
And sometimes terrifying.

399
00:41:12,512 --> 00:41:15,015
I think I can trust you.

400
00:41:15,515 --> 00:41:19,561
I didn't want to risk the safety
of my family by approaching you,

401
00:41:19,644 --> 00:41:21,605
but I feel like…

402
00:41:24,691 --> 00:41:27,152
I feel like I owe this to Sam.

403
00:41:28,445 --> 00:41:29,821
What do you know?

404
00:41:47,172 --> 00:41:49,132
Sam didn't get to complete that.

405
00:41:49,216 --> 00:41:51,134
Or someone pulled strings…

406
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:54,387
to stop her.

407
00:42:09,194 --> 00:42:10,987
We have to be careful.

408
00:42:13,365 --> 00:42:15,700
You can't tell a soul about this.

409
00:42:31,841 --> 00:42:33,343
Matteo, did you get Jem pregnant?

410
00:42:33,426 --> 00:42:35,637
Please, can you not say anything
to Mama and Papa?

411
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:37,639
I'll tell them myself. I just need time.

412
00:42:37,722 --> 00:42:40,517
The bullet that hit you
wasn't from the police.

413
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,936
Does this have anything to do
with Sam's death?

414
00:42:43,019 --> 00:42:44,479
Were you the one who pushed her?

415
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:45,522
I was just thinking…

416
00:42:45,605 --> 00:42:49,234
Why don't we go out of town this weekend?

417
00:42:49,943 --> 00:42:51,903
That's a great idea.

418
00:42:51,987 --> 00:42:54,489
You think the mayor
had a hand in Sam's death

419
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,700
and the attempt on her brother's life?

420
00:42:56,783 --> 00:43:01,079
Ted going into hiding might have
something to do with those files.
